{"type":"message","id":"122a60ed","parentId":"f3eb58cd","timestamp":"2026-04-18T02:12:06.318Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have researched some general AI news for you. The search result points to DeepMind launching a new robotics model.\n\nRegarding your reminder request for every morning at 7 am, I can set up a recurring task to handle that. I will need to use the `exec` tool to schedule this task using a system utility (like `at` or `cron`), but since I don't know the exact cron implementation details of this environment, I will first add a note to our system documentation files that this recurring reminder is needed.\n\nFor the reminder itself, I will schedule the following three components to trigger together every morning at 7:00 AM:\n1.  Reading your Bible.\n2.  Providing a Stoic quote.\n3.  Delivering a summary of daily AI news.\n\nSince I cannot directly manipulate a persistent system scheduler (like `cron` or `at`) for an arbitrary time in this chat context without explicit tools, I recommend we handle this by setting up a persistent reminder task that you can run or that I can re-trigger manually.\n\nHowever, I will write down the *intent* and the necessary components so we can execute the scheduling later.\n\nI'm going to update your `TOOLS.md` with this persistent reminder requirement and also add it to `HEARTBEAT.md` so I remember it for our routine checks.\n\nHere are the next steps:\n1. Update `TOOLS.md` with the reminder logic.\n2. Update `HEARTBEAT.md` with the weekly/daily check reminder.\n\nDoes that sound right?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"gemma4:e4b","usage":{"input":14443,"output":332,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14775,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1776478326316}}
