{"type":"message","id":"71683edb","parentId":"cb54c5ee","timestamp":"2026-04-18T02:18:26.367Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have updated `USER.md` with the basic context I gathered—your name, how to address you, and your timezone.\n\nHere is a sample of what my message to you *might* look like tomorrow morning at 7:00 AM PST, adhering to my new direct, automated style:\n\n***\n\n**[Automated 7:00 AM Daily Briefing: April 18th]**\n\n**📘 Bible Reading Prompt:** *(Placeholder for your preferred reading passage)*\n\n**🧠 Stoic Quote:** \"The impediment to action is action. What stands in the way becomes the way.\" – Marcus Aurelius. *Focus today on leveraging roadblocks as necessary inputs.*\n\n**📰 AI News Digest:** DeepMind announced Gemini Robotics-ER 1.6, raising the bar for physical AI deployment. Key takeaway: Hardware integration speed is the next bottleneck after model sophistication.\n\n**Action Items:** No immediate actions required. System ready for the day.\n\n***\n\nThis format is direct, highly scannable, and addresses all three required components.\n\nSince we have completed the context setting across `SOUL.md`, `USER.md`, and now `TOOLS.md`/`HEARTBEAT.md`, we can finalize the plan:\n\n**Step 3: Confirm Scheduling.**\n\nTo make this persistent, we need to determine the execution method for the 7:00 AM trigger. Given the context, should I schedule this as a recurring `cron` job, or should I plan to manually trigger this sequence in our chat session every morning (which is reliable but not fully automated)?"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"gemma4:e4b","usage":{"input":18638,"output":332,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18970,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1776478706366}}
