{"type":"message","id":"9c866075","parentId":"e369aa8d","timestamp":"2026-04-22T03:02:19.033Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:8072905176\",\n  \"message_id\": \"189\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8072905176\",\n  \"sender\": \"D Sanders\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Tue 2026-04-21 20:02 PDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"D Sanders (8072905176)\",\n  \"id\": \"8072905176\",\n  \"name\": \"D Sanders\",\n  \"username\": \"dsand310\"\n}\n```\n\nMy role at work is head of technology customer operations. I am the leader of 1 of 13 nodes who provide IT support, implementation and change request for a specific group of customers. Macys is one of my customer. They have a sub customer named Lego. We have been having issues with Lego freight because it appears some cartons have too many labels which causes the sortation system to reject the cartons. At work we have several systems, I primary use SQL, our internal preparatory system(webec) and Scale."}],"timestamp":1776826939032}}
